00:46:38.370 --> 00:46:40.150
Here's the thing.

00:46:40.150 --> 00:46:43.710
The way the banking system works
is if I go to a bank and

00:46:43.710 --> 00:46:48.310
I put $100 into the
bank, there's a

00:46:48.310 --> 00:46:50.120
credit for me for $100.

00:46:50.120 --> 00:46:52.820
So say I'm a bank and
you give me $100.

00:46:52.820 --> 00:46:55.420
You've now got $100, but it
happens to be in the bank.

00:46:55.420 --> 00:46:57.260
I then have to keep,
say, 5% of that.

00:46:57.260 --> 00:46:58.750
So I keep $5 in the bank.

00:46:58.750 --> 00:47:02.400
And I can turn around and
I can lend you $95.

00:47:02.400 --> 00:47:07.210
So now there's $200
in the system.

00:47:07.210 --> 00:47:09.060
And then you can go and give
it to another bank.

00:47:09.060 --> 00:47:11.410
And suddenly we start to see
exponentially the amount of

00:47:11.410 --> 00:47:13.140
money that there is
in the system.

00:47:13.140 --> 00:47:15.150
A lot of this is just
notional money.

00:47:15.150 --> 00:47:18.880
Because there's only-- if you
came to me today and said, I

00:47:18.880 --> 00:47:21.520
want my $100 back,
I'd be like, OK.

00:47:21.520 --> 00:47:22.870
And I'd have to turn around
and borrow it

00:47:22.870 --> 00:47:24.180
from somebody else.

00:47:24.180 --> 00:47:28.450
And this is slightly away from
your question, but what

00:47:28.450 --> 00:47:30.130
happens in the banking
system is that this

00:47:30.130 --> 00:47:30.960
happens all the time.

00:47:30.960 --> 00:47:33.340
Banks run out of money.

00:47:33.340 --> 00:47:34.690
It sounds absurd, right?

00:47:34.690 --> 00:47:35.680
But they actually run
out of money.

00:47:35.680 --> 00:47:38.590
So they have to go to other
banks to borrow money.

00:47:38.590 --> 00:47:41.140
So say, for example, this is
what happened in Lehman

00:47:41.140 --> 00:47:42.070
Brothers-- well, no.

00:47:42.070 --> 00:47:43.680
That's not a good example
because Lehman Brothers was

00:47:43.680 --> 00:47:44.680
not a commercial bank.

00:47:44.680 --> 00:47:46.170
But say, for example,
I'm the bank.

00:47:46.170 --> 00:47:47.190
You want your money from me.

00:47:47.190 --> 00:47:48.300
I have to go to another bank.

00:47:48.300 --> 00:47:51.610
And that bank says to me, no.

00:47:51.610 --> 00:47:53.460
I'm not going to lend you
that money overnight.

00:47:53.460 --> 00:47:54.450
Because they usually do
it in what's called

00:47:54.450 --> 00:47:55.410
the overnight market.

00:47:55.410 --> 00:47:57.400
The bank says to me--

00:47:57.400 --> 00:47:59.160
J.P. Morgan says to me, I'm not
lending the Bank of Paddy

00:47:59.160 --> 00:48:02.780
Hirsch money overnight,
because I think you're

00:48:02.780 --> 00:48:05.610
invested in really
dodgy securities.

00:48:05.610 --> 00:48:06.080
What do you mean.

00:48:06.080 --> 00:48:08.170
Said, well, if you're invested
in bad securities, it means

00:48:08.170 --> 00:48:09.780
that you're not going to
be able to redeem those

00:48:09.780 --> 00:48:10.730
securities for any money.

00:48:10.730 --> 00:48:12.140
Which means you're not going
to be able to pay me

00:48:12.140 --> 00:48:13.550
back, let alone you.

00:48:13.550 --> 00:48:16.770
So suddenly I'm bust.

00:48:16.770 --> 00:48:17.840
Nobody's lending me any money.

00:48:17.840 --> 00:48:19.660
I owe you $95.

00:48:19.660 --> 00:48:20.990
I can give you $5.

00:48:20.990 --> 00:48:22.520
Sorry.

00:48:22.520 --> 00:48:23.950
But I'm bust.

00:48:23.950 --> 00:48:27.260
And that's really the root cause
of what happened when we

00:48:27.260 --> 00:48:29.600
were worried about the financial
system collapsing.

00:48:29.600 --> 00:48:31.570
It was the fact that these
banks would not

00:48:31.570 --> 00:48:32.440
lend to each other.

00:48:32.440 --> 00:48:34.950
And if banks stop lending to
each other, it's like you stop

00:48:34.950 --> 00:48:37.040
the flow of blood
around the body.

00:48:37.040 --> 00:48:38.780
And suddenly you have-- you know
what it's like when you

00:48:38.780 --> 00:48:41.320
stop blood flowing around a
body, is bits of the body

00:48:41.320 --> 00:48:41.950
start to drop off.

00:48:41.950 --> 00:48:45.250
They get gangrenous and horrible
and they fall off.

00:48:45.250 --> 00:48:48.270
So that's really what happened,
is the lifeblood

00:48:48.270 --> 00:48:50.690
started to slow down and
maybe even stop.

00:48:50.690 --> 00:48:55.120
And the urgency was keeping
that lifeblood going.

00:48:55.120 --> 00:48:56.790
But you had another question,
which was, where

00:48:56.790 --> 00:48:57.690
did that money go?

